[The Global Influenza Programme monitors influenza activity worldwide and publishes an update every 2 weeks. The updates are based on available epidemiological and virological data sources, including FluNet (reported by the WHO Global Influenza Surveillance and Response System) and influenza reports from WHO Regional Offices and Member States. Completeness can vary among updates due to availability and quality of data available at the time when the update is developed.

For updates on influenza at the human-animal interface, see the following WHO web pages: Influenza at the Human-Animal Interface (HAI) and Disease outbreak news.

Interested readers are advised to consult the original document via the source URL to view the above information in diagrammatic form. Overall, the northern hemisphere epidemic has declined to the background level, whereas the Southern hemisphere epidemic is progressing sporadically, with some parts of Southern America having a predominance of RSV and adenovirus over influenza viruses. In Southern Africa, the epidemic has yet to begin. - Mod.CP]
